2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of Grassmannians, Schubert divisors, and their automorphism groups, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses results on the automorphism group of the big cell of a Grassmannian, which is a topic in computational geometry. 
4. cs.GR (Group Theory) - The paper involves the study of automorphism groups of codes and Grassmannians, which are topics in group theory. 
5. cs.CO (Combinatorics) - The paper uses combinatorial techniques to analyze the automorphism groups of Grassmann codes and Schubert divisors.
